#compdef qmlimportscanner
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# qt/qtdeclarative tools/qmlimportscanner/main.cpp.  Reference
# accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
#
# qmlimportscanner is the only Qt-tools tool not yet covered in
# the corpus alongside _qmlformat, _qmllint, _qmlls,
# _qmlprofiler, _qmltestrunner, _qmltc, _qmlcachegen,
# _qmltyperegistrar, _qmlplugindump, _qmlscene.  It walks a QML
# source tree (or list of QML / JS / QRC files) and emits the
# transitive import graph as JSON (default) or CMake content
# (`-cmake-output`).  Used by the Qt CMake build system to
# auto-detect QML plugin dependencies during qt_add_qml_module.
#
# Critical extraction note: qmlimportscanner does NOT use
# QCommandLineParser despite being a Qt tool — main.cpp:856
# comment explains:
#   "@file" doesn't start with a '-' so we can't use
#   QCommandLineParser for it
# Instead the tool implements its own argv-walking loop at
# main.cpp:906-972 with explicit `if (arg == "-rootPath")` arm
# tests.  This gives it two non-QCommandLineParser features:
#   (a) Qt single-dash long-form options (e.g. `-rootPath` NOT
#       `--rootPath`)
#   (b) @-prefixed response-file argument expansion at
#       argumentsFromCommandLineAndFile() main.cpp:852-879
# Completion uses single-dash long-form consistently.
#
# Critical extraction note: 5 of the 9 flags are
# MULTI-ARGUMENT GREEDY — the inner while-loop at main.cpp:955-
# 971 consumes ALL subsequent non-dash args into the receiver
# vector until the next dash-prefixed flag.  Example:
#   qmlimportscanner -rootPath a/ b/ c/ -importPath /qt/qml
# puts a/, b/, c/ all into qmlRootPaths.  Completion uses `*`
# repeatable + single-value-per-occurrence since either pattern
# (`-flag a -flag b` OR `-flag a b`) is valid per the parser.

_arguments \
  \*'-rootPath+[QML source directory to scan (multi-value or repeat)]:dir:_files -/' \
  \*'-qmlFiles+[QML file to scan (multi-value or repeat)]:file:_files -g "*.qml"' \
  \*'-jsFiles+[JavaScript file to scan (multi-value or repeat)]:file:_files -g "*.(js|mjs)"' \
  \*'-importPath+[Qt QML import path (typically the QML2_IMPORT_PATH; multi-value or repeat)]:dir:_files -/' \
  \*'-qrcFiles+[Qt resource file to scan (multi-value or repeat)]:qrc:_files -g "*.qrc"' \
  \*'-exclude+[exclude directory from scan (multi-value or repeat; no file-exists check)]:dir:_files -/' \
  '-cmake-output[emit CMake content instead of JSON (default)]' \
  '-output-file+[write output to FILE instead of stdout]:file:_files' \
  '-add-version[include QML import version info in output]' \
  '*:rootPath OR @response-file (bare arg appended to qmlRootPaths; "@file" reads args from file):_files'
